    "body": "Some feedback on the highlight, I think this is a bit too contrasted in terms of information hierarchy, and makes the highlighted parts look like buttons.\r\n\r\nWhat do you think of going with something like this instead?\r\n\r\n<img width=\"223\" alt=\"Capture d’écran 2025-03-03 à 11 22 32\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/cf19424a-cc19-4571-8c35-677a52f47e8c\" />\r\n\r\n<img width=\"223\" alt=\"Capture d’écran 2025-03-03 à 11 22 52\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2461846c-4307-4452-95e3-2715f2f48a77\" />\r\n\r\nUsed values:\r\n\r\n```css\r\nbackground-color: rgba(var(--ais-primary-color-rgb), 0.2); /* 0.1 in light mode */\r\ncolor: rgba(var(--ais-primary-color-rgb), var(--ais-primary-color-alpha));\r\nborder-radius: 2px; /* we don't have to use the same radius as for buttons, it makes sense for customers to want to change them independently */\r\n```\r\n\r\nThoughts?",
