    "body": "> Some feedback on the highlight, I think this is a bit too contrasted in terms of information hierarchy, and makes the highlighted parts look like buttons.\r\n> \r\n> What do you think of going with something like this instead?\r\n> \r\n> <img alt=\"Capture d’écran 2025-03-03 à 11 22 32\" width=\"223\" src=\"https://private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/5370675/418531785-cf19424a-cc19-4571-8c35-677a52f47e8c.png?jwt=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..rnI9VopdfTBgHna9lx_P-mpoc1iQ2wK-WJuphJN5iOs\"> <img alt=\"Capture d’écran 2025-03-03 à 11 22 52\" width=\"223\" src=\"https://private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/5370675/418531796-2461846c-4307-4452-95e3-2715f2f48a77.png?jwt=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..PKb52zp0RRkYeTVlYatPiS917RNLsSz7eVUS1JkVFfA\">\r\n> Used values:\r\n> \r\n> ```css\r\n> background-color: rgba(var(--ais-primary-color-rgb), 0.2); /* 0.1 in light mode */\r\n> color: rgba(var(--ais-primary-color-rgb), var(--ais-primary-color-alpha));\r\n> border-radius: 2px; /* we don't have to use the same radius as for buttons, it makes sense for customers to want to change them independently */\r\n> ```\r\n> \r\n> Thoughts?\r\n\r\nGood call, thanks!",
